(*4): “Pre-incubation” option stimulates an initial stage of the amplification to allow stable amplification of the circular DNA particularly when the amplification is difficult due to a low amount of the template DNA molecules. 



 ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":53}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"dj7g9","text":"Add 1 μl of the assembly product (or oriC circular DNA), and mix with pipetting (*3). Incubate the mixture at 33°C for 6 hours(*5) and hold at 12'C (*6) or on ice before use. 
(*5): ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":0,"length":175}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6oomf","text":" The incubation time can be shortened to 3 hours particularly when already supercoiled DNA is used as a template. The 6 hours incubation allows stable amplification particularly of the assembly product which requires gap-repair process. ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5nd31","text":"Higher temperature up to 40'C or longer incubation up to 16 hours is acceptable, but tends to produce other short DNA byproduct than your target. ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"6fae5","text":"(*6): ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"align-left","offset":0,"length":6}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"5097s","text":"A thermal cycler program is useful to hold automatically at 12°C after the 33°C incubation. 




","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"align-left","offset":0,"length":97}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

